# GitHub Packages Configuration
#
# To publish to GitHub Packages, you need to authenticate with a GitHub Personal Access Token.
#
# Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file to .npmrc (it's in .gitignore, so it won't be committed)
# 2. Replace YOUR_GITHUB_TOKEN with your actual token
# 3. Create a token at: https://github.com/settings/tokens/new
#    Required scopes: write:packages, read:packages
#
# For local publishing:
@ibrahimcesar:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com
//npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=YOUR_GITHUB_TOKEN

# For installation (consumers of your package):
# Users installing your package need to add this to their .npmrc:
# @ibrahimcesar:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com
# //npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=THEIR_GITHUB_TOKEN
